In this op-ed, Vice President Mike Pence discusses the benefits of the recent tax reform law signed by President Trump. He highlights the increased tax cuts for families, including a higher tax-free income threshold and an expanded child tax credit. Pence also mentions the simplification of the tax filing process, with the possibility of filing taxes on a single sheet of paper. He emphasizes the elimination of the individual mandate tax under Obamacare and the positive impact of tax cuts for businesses, leading to bonuses and raises for workers. Pence claims that these tax cuts will result in a pay raise of $4,000 for working families in the future. He also mentions other achievements of the Trump administration, such as rolling back federal regulations, utilizing natural resources, and prioritizing fair trade agreements.